subject: p12595991
Findings: Left-sided AICD/pacemaker device is noted with leads terminating in the right atrium, right ventricle, and coronary sinus, unchanged. Mild enlargement of the cardiac silhouette is stable, with aortic knob calcifications re-demonstrated. The pulmonary vascularity is normal, and the lungs are clear. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is present. There are mild degenerative changes in the thoracic spine with anterior bridging osteophytes.
